Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive report.

## OpenClaw Channel Plugin Structure Report

I've thoroughly explored the OpenClaw repository structure for channel plugins. Here's a comprehensive guide to help you create the PulseBoard channel plugin.

---

### 1. WORKSPACE STRUCTURE & PACKAGE CONFIGURATION

**Workspace Root Config:**
- **File:** `/pnpm-workspace.yaml`
  - Configures monorepo with: `[., ui, packages/*, extensions/*]`
  - All channel plugins live in the `extensions/` directory

**Root Package.json:**
- **File:** `/package.json` (version 2026.4.2)
  - Workspace name: `"openclaw"`
  - Contains exports for plugin-sdk subpaths (core, runtime, setup, etc.)
  - Each subpath export points to compiled `.d.ts` and `.js` files

---

### 2. EXISTING CHANNEL PLUGINS DIRECTORY STRUCTURE

I found 90+ channel plugin extensions. Three representative examples:

#### **IRC Plugin** (`/extensions/irc/`)
Structure:
```
extensions/irc/
├── package.json                 # Package metadata
├── openclaw.plugin.json         # Plugin manifest
├── index.ts                     # Main entry point
├── setup-entry.ts              # Setup-only entry point
├── api.ts                       # Public API exports
├── channel-config-api.ts        # Channel config API
├── runtime-api.ts              # Runtime API
└── src/
    ├── channel.ts              # Main plugin definition
    ├── runtime.ts              # Runtime singleton setup
    ├── types.ts                # Type definitions
    ├── accounts.ts             # Account resolution logic
    ├── config-schema.ts        # Config validation
    ├── setup-core.ts           # Setup adapter
    ├── setup-surface.ts        # Setup UI/wizard
    ├── send.ts                 # Outbound message sending
    ├── inbound.ts              # Inbound message handling
    ├── normalize.ts            # Target normalization
    ├── monitor.ts              # Connection monitoring
    ├── probe.ts                # Connection probing
    ├── policy.ts               # Security policy
    ├── protocol.ts             # Protocol handling
    └── [test files...]
```

#### **Telegram Plugin** (`/extensions/telegram/`)
- Much more complex (90+ files in src/)
- Structure similar to IRC but with many additional features:
  - Bot handlers, media processing, approvals system
  - Native commands, inline buttons, reactions
  - Thread bindings, session management
  - Webhook support, polling support

#### **Discord Plugin** (`/extensions/discord/`)
- Similar pattern to Telegram (complexity varies by feature set)

---

### 3. PACKAGE.JSON CONFIGURATION

**IRC Example:**
```json
{
  "name": "@openclaw/irc",
  "version": "2026.4.1-beta.1",
  "description": "OpenClaw IRC channel plugin",
  "type": "module",
  "openclaw": {
    "extensions": ["./index.ts"],
    "setupEntry": "./setup-entry.ts",
    "install": {
      "minHostVersion": ">=2026.4.1"
    },
    "channel": {
      "id": "irc",
      "label": "IRC",
      "selectionLabel": "IRC (Server + Nick)",
      "detailLabel": "IRC",
      "docsPath": "/channels/irc",
      "docsLabel": "irc",
      "blurb": "classic IRC networks with DM/channel routing and pairing controls.",
      "aliases": ["internet-relay-chat"],
      "systemImage": "network"
    }
  }
}
```

**Telegram Example (with dependencies):**
```json
{
  "name": "@openclaw/telegram",
  "version": "2026.4.1-beta.1",
  "private": true,
  "description": "OpenClaw Telegram channel plugin",
  "type": "module",
  "dependencies": {
    "@grammyjs/runner": "^2.0.3",
    "@grammyjs/transformer-throttler": "^1.2.1",
    "grammy": "^1.41.1"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "openclaw": "workspace:*"
  },
  "peerDependencies": {
    "openclaw": ">=2026.4.1-beta.1"
  },
  "peerDependenciesMeta": {
    "openclaw": {
      "optional": true
    }
  },
  "openclaw": {
    "extensions": ["./index.ts"],
    "setupEntry": "./setup-entry.ts",
    "channel": {
      "id": "telegram",
      "label": "Telegram",
      "selectionLabel": "Telegram (Bot API)",
      "detailLabel": "Telegram Bot",
      "docsPath": "/channels/telegram",
      "docsLabel": "telegram",
      "blurb": "simplest way to get started — register a bot with @BotFather and get going.",
      "systemImage": "paperplane",
      "markdownCapable": true
    },
    "bundle": {
      "stageRuntimeDependencies": true
    }
  }
}
```

**Key Fields:**
- `"type": "module"` - ES modules required
- `openclaw.extensions` - Array of entry point files
- `openclaw.setupEntry` - Setup-only entry (separate from main entry)
- `openclaw.channel` - Metadata for UI/docs/selection
- `openclaw.install` - Version constraints, npm spec, defaults
- `openclaw.bundle` - Optional bundling hints
- `openclaw.release` - Publishing to npm (optional)

---

### 4. OPENCLAW.PLUGIN.JSON MANIFEST

**IRC Example:**
```json
{
  "id": "irc",
  "channels": ["irc"],
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

**Telegram Example:**
```json
{
  "id": "telegram",
  "channels": ["telegram"],
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

**Fields:**
- `id` - Plugin identifier (lowercase, matches package name suffix)
- `channels` - Array of channel names this plugin provides
- `configSchema` - JSON Schema for plugin-level configuration (not channel config)

---

### 5. ENTRY POINT FILES

#### **index.ts (Main Entry Point)**

**IRC Pattern:**
```typescript
import type { ChannelPlugin } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { defineChannelPluginEntry } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { ircPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";
import { setIrcRuntime } from "./src/runtime.js";

export { ircPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";
export { setIrcRuntime } from "./src/runtime.js";

export default defineChannelPluginEntry({
  id: "irc",
  name: "IRC",
  description: "IRC channel plugin",
  plugin: ircPlugin as ChannelPlugin,
  setRuntime: setIrcRuntime,
});
```

**Telegram Pattern (with registerFull):**
```typescript
import { defineChannelPluginEntry } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { telegramPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";
import { setTelegramRuntime } from "./src/runtime.js";

export { telegramPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";
export { setTelegramRuntime } from "./src/runtime.js";

export default defineChannelPluginEntry({
  id: "telegram",
  name: "Telegram",
  description: "Telegram channel plugin",
  plugin: telegramPlugin,
  setRuntime: setTelegramRuntime,
});
```

**defineChannelPluginEntry Options:**
- `id` - Channel identifier
- `name` - Display name
- `description` - Brief description
- `plugin` - The ChannelPlugin implementation
- `setRuntime?` - Optional runtime setter function
- `configSchema?` - Optional plugin-level config schema
- `registerCliMetadata?` - Optional CLI metadata registration
- `registerFull?` - Optional full-runtime registration (additional hooks)

#### **setup-entry.ts (Setup-Only Entry Point)**

**IRC Pattern:**
```typescript
import { defineSetupPluginEntry } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { ircPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";

export default defineSetupPluginEntry(ircPlugin);
```

**Telegram Pattern:**
```typescript
import { defineSetupPluginEntry } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { telegramSetupPlugin } from "./src/channel.setup.js";

export { telegramSetupPlugin } from "./src/channel.setup.js";

export default defineSetupPluginEntry(telegramSetupPlugin);
```

---

### 6. KEY SOURCE FILE PATTERNS

#### **runtime.ts - Runtime Singleton Setup**

**Pattern (IRC):**
```typescript
import { createPluginRuntimeStore } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store";
import type { PluginRuntime } from "./runtime-api.js";

const { setRuntime: setIrcRuntime, getRuntime: getIrcRuntime } =
  createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>("IRC runtime not initialized");

export { getIrcRuntime, setIrcRuntime };

export function clearIrcRuntime() {
  setIrcRuntime(undefined as unknown as PluginRuntime);
}
```

**Key Pattern:**
- Uses `createPluginRuntimeStore()` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store`
- Provides getter/setter for typed runtime object
- Runtime is initialized during full app startup (after CLI setup mode)

#### **types.ts - Configuration Types**

**IRC Example Structure:**
```typescript
// Channel-level config
export type IrcChannelConfig = {
  requireMention?: boolean;
  tools?: GroupToolPolicyConfig;
  enabled?: boolean;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  systemPrompt?: string;
};

// Account-level config
export type IrcAccountConfig = {
  name?: string;
  enabled?: boolean;
  host?: string;
  port?: number;
  tls?: boolean;
  nick?: string;
  username?: string;
  password?: string;
  dmPolicy?: DmPolicy;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  groups?: Record<string, IrcChannelConfig>;
  channels?: string[];
  // ... more fields
};

// Top-level channel config
export type IrcConfig = IrcAccountConfig & {
  accounts?: Record<string, IrcAccountConfig>;
  defaultAccount?: string;
};

// Integration into OpenClawConfig
export type CoreConfig = OpenClawConfig & {
  channels?: OpenClawConfig["channels"] & {
    irc?: IrcConfig;
  };
};

// Domain-specific message type
export type IrcInboundMessage = {
  messageId: string;
  target: string; // Channel name for groups, nick for DMs
  senderNick: string;
  text: string;
  timestamp: number;
  isGroup: boolean;
};

// Probe result for testing connectivity
export type IrcProbe = BaseProbeResult<string> & {
  host: string;
  port: number;
  tls: boolean;
  nick: string;
  latencyMs?: number;
};
```

#### **src/channel.ts - Main Plugin Definition**

**Pattern Used (Telegram as example):**
```typescript
import { createChatChannelPlugin } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
// ... many imports from openclaw/plugin-sdk/* and local modules

export const telegramPlugin = createChatChannelPlugin({
  base: {
    id: "telegram",
    meta: { /* channel metadata */ },
    capabilities: { /* feature flags */ },
    setup: telegramSetupAdapter,
    config: telegramConfigAdapter,
    // ... other optional fields
  },
  security: {
    dm: {
      channelKey: "telegram",
      resolvePolicy: (account) => account.config.dmPolicy,
      resolveAllowFrom: (account) => account.config.allowFrom,
      // ... other security config
    }
  },
  pairing: {
    text: {
      idLabel: "Telegram chat ID",
      message: PAIRING_APPROVED_MESSAGE,
      notify: async (ctx) => { /* send approval message */ }
    }
  },
  threading: {
    scopedAccountReplyToMode: {
      resolveAccount: resolveTelegramAccount,
      resolveReplyToMode: (account) => account.config.replyToMode,
    }
  },
  outbound: {
    attachedResults: {
      channel: "telegram",
      sendText: sendMessageTelegram,
      sendMedia: sendMediaTelegram,
      sendPoll: sendPollTelegram,
    }
  }
});
```

---

### 7. PLUGIN SDK CONTRACT TYPES

#### **ChannelPlugin Type** (`src/channels/plugins/types.plugin.ts`)

```typescript
export type ChannelPlugin<ResolvedAccount = any, Probe = unknown, Audit = unknown> = {
  id: ChannelId;
  meta: ChannelMeta;
  capabilities: ChannelCapabilities;

  // Optional configuration
  defaults?: {
    queue?: { debounceMs?: number };
  };
  reload?: { configPrefixes: string[]; noopPrefixes?: string[] };

  // Setup and config
  setupWizard?: ChannelSetupWizard | ChannelSetupWizardAdapter;
  config: ChannelConfigAdapter<ResolvedAccount>;
  configSchema?: ChannelConfigSchema;
  setup?: ChannelSetupAdapter;

  // Security & Access Control
  pairing?: ChannelPairingAdapter;
  security?: ChannelSecurityAdapter<ResolvedAccount>;
  groups?: ChannelGroupAdapter;
  mentions?: ChannelMentionAdapter;
  allowlist?: ChannelAllowlistAdapter;

  // Message handling
  outbound?: ChannelOutboundAdapter;
  status?: ChannelStatusAdapter<ResolvedAccount, Probe, Audit>;
  streaming?: ChannelStreamingAdapter;
  threading?: ChannelThreadingAdapter;
  messaging?: ChannelMessagingAdapter;

  // Advanced features
  gatewayMethods?: string[];
  gateway?: ChannelGatewayAdapter<ResolvedAccount>;
  auth?: ChannelAuthAdapter;
  approvalCapability?: ChannelApprovalCapability;
  approvals?: ChannelApprovalAdapter;
  elevated?: ChannelElevatedAdapter;
  commands?: ChannelCommandAdapter;
  lifecycle?: ChannelLifecycleAdapter;
  conversationBindings?: ChannelConversationBindingSupport;

  // Tools & Actions
  agentPrompt?: ChannelAgentPromptAdapter;
  agentTools?: ChannelAgentToolFactory | ChannelAgentTool[];
  actions?: ChannelMessageActionAdapter;

  // Misc
  directory?: ChannelDirectoryAdapter;
  resolver?: ChannelResolverAdapter;
  heartbeat?: ChannelHeartbeatAdapter;
  bindings?: ChannelConfiguredBindingProvider;
};
```

#### **ChannelMeta Type** (User-facing metadata)
```typescript
export type ChannelMeta = {
  id: ChannelId;
  label: string;                      // "IRC"
  selectionLabel: string;             // "IRC (Server + Nick)"
  docsPath: string;                   // "/channels/irc"
  docsLabel?: string;                 // "irc"
  blurb: string;                      // "classic IRC networks..."
  order?: number;
  aliases?: readonly string[];
  detailLabel?: string;               // "IRC"
  systemImage?: string;               // SF Symbols name
  markdownCapable?: boolean;
  showConfigured?: boolean;
  quickstartAllowFrom?: boolean;
  forceAccountBinding?: boolean;
  preferSessionLookupForAnnounceTarget?: boolean;
  preferOver?: readonly string[];
};
```

#### **ChannelConfigSchema**
```typescript
export type ChannelConfigSchema = {
  schema: Record<string, unknown>;    // JSON Schema
  uiHints?: Record<string, ChannelConfigUiHint>;
  runtime?: ChannelConfigRuntimeSchema;
};

export type ChannelConfigUiHint = {
  label?: string;
  help?: string;
  tags?: string[];
  advanced?: boolean;
  sensitive?: boolean;
  placeholder?: string;
  itemTemplate?: unknown;
};
```

---

### 8. CREATING CHANNELPLUGIN WITH createChatChannelPlugin HELPER

**Function Signature:**
```typescript
export function createChatChannelPlugin<
  TResolvedAccount extends { accountId?: string | null },
  Probe = unknown,
  Audit = unknown,
>(params: {
  base: ChatChannelPluginBase<TResolvedAccount, Probe, Audit>;
  security?: ChannelSecurityAdapter<TResolvedAccount> | ChatChannelSecurityOptions<TResolvedAccount>;
  pairing?: ChannelPairingAdapter | ChatChannelPairingOptions;
  threading?: ChannelThreadingAdapter | ChatChannelThreadingOptions<TResolvedAccount>;
  outbound?: ChannelOutboundAdapter | ChatChannelAttachedOutboundOptions;
}): ChannelPlugin<TResolvedAccount, Probe, Audit>
```

**What it does:**
- Automatically adds `conversationBindings: { supportsCurrentConversationBinding: true }`
- Resolves simplified security/pairing/threading/outbound options
- Fills in sensible defaults for chat-style channels
- Returns fully formed ChannelPlugin object

---

### 9. PLUGIN SDK IMPORTS

**Standard imports for channel plugins:**
```typescript
// Core plugin registration
import { defineChannelPluginEntry, createChatChannelPlugin } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { defineSetupPluginEntry } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";

// Runtime & status
import { createPluginRuntimeStore } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store";
import { createComputedAccountStatusAdapter } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/status-helpers";

// Config & setup
import { createScopedChannelConfigAdapter } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-helpers";
import { createChannelDirectoryAdapter } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/directory-runtime";

// Security & pairing
import { createAllowlistProviderOpenWarningCollector } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-policy";
import { createPairingPrefixStripper } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-pairing";

// Outbound messaging
import { resolveOutboundSendDep } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/outbound-runtime";
import { attachChannelToResult } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-send-result";

// Routing
import { buildOutboundBaseSessionKey } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/routing";

// Helpers
import { getChatChannelMeta } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
```

**Avoid importing from:**
- `src/**` (internals)
- `src/channels/**` (channel internals)
- `src/plugin-sdk-internal/**`
- Other extension's `src/**` directories

---

### 10. KEY ADAPTER INTERFACES

All these are imported from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core` → src/channels/plugins/types.*.ts:

- **ChannelConfigAdapter** - Read/write config for accounts
